[Tom Ridge, director of the the new White House Office of Homeland Security,
coming to the foreground in this matter is welcomed by all of us, and we
wish him well. Coordination is long overdue. And I hope he organises a
thorough post-mortem when the dust settles. We have been given a great
opportunity to make mistakes with minimal cost.
I am told by David Ashford, CDC, that some person is recommending that those
with inhalation anthrax be vaccinated. As such clinical patients would
already be undergoing antibiotic treatment I think we can assume that they
will, if they survive, generate a perfectly adequate immune response without
benefit of vaccination. - Mod.MHJ
